Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on a rocky outcrop showing the pecked figures of two unidentified quadrupeds, both upright and facing left. The figure on the lower left appears to be a caprid (ibex? goat?) with short, backward-sweeping horns The other figure, to the upper right, has a large body with short legs and a long thick neck (giraffe) and has pecked spotted coat pattern markings. Western Desert, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
